                            <comment id="15173028" author="pauloricardomg" created="Tue, 1 Mar 2016 01:07:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Overall LGTM, but how about moving the actual logging to &lt;tt&gt;DatabaseDescriptor&lt;/tt&gt; so we don&apos;t need to change the &lt;tt&gt;ConfigurationLoader&lt;/tt&gt; interface and we&apos;ll also log configuration of custom loaders? We could also maybe save the latest loaded configuration and print only in case the configuration changed, since that could still be useful to operators (though this will probably only happen when refreshing seeds currently), WDYT?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The log &lt;tt&gt;INFO  [main] 2016-02-29 21:59:21,025 YamlConfigurationLoader.java:92 - Loading settings from &lt;a href=&quot;file:~/.ccm/test/node1/conf/cassandra.yaml&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;file:~/.ccm/test/node1/conf/cassandra.yaml&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; is still being print repeatedly, should we maybe decrease the log level to &lt;tt&gt;DEBUG&lt;/tt&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15174689" author="jasobrown" created="Wed, 2 Mar 2016 00:25:03 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;how about moving the actual logging to &lt;tt&gt;DatabaseDescriptor&lt;/tt&gt; so we don&apos;t need to change the &lt;tt&gt;ConfigurationLoader&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Good call. I&apos;ve moved the logging into &lt;tt&gt;Config#log&lt;/tt&gt;, and is still invoked from DD the way it was in the first patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;maybe decrease the log level to &lt;tt&gt;DEBUG&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Done.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tests running now.&lt;/p&gt;

